<p>There are lots of other ways to add color to your tooltips: You can try <strong>colored shapes next to the text</strong>, or a <strong>background color for the whole or just part of the tooltip.</strong></p>



<p>All the tooltips you can see here are created with HTML code like I showed you above. If you&#39;re using Datawrapper, you can see all the code snippets and their explanations in our Academy articles <a href="https://academy.datawrapper.de/article/237-i-want-to-change-how-my-data-appears-in-tooltips" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><strong>How to customize tooltips</strong></a> and <a href="https://academy.datawrapper.de/article/282-how-to-embed-charts-into-tooltips" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><strong>How to add charts to tooltips</strong></a>.</p>



