<p>(When trying this approach, keep in mind that <strong>blue text will be perceived as a link</strong>. If you’re using blue for a category and then use it as a text color, it might confuse readers.)</p>



<p>Including a color key in the surrounding article — and hence creating a deeper integration between article and visualization — seems to be less common. Here are two attempts, but both keep a traditional color key as well:</p>



